The '1979â80 FA Cup' was the 99th season of the world's oldest football knockout
competition, 'The Football Association Challenge Cup', or FA Cup. The final saw
second division West Ham United beat holders Arsenal 1-0. As of 2013, this was
the last occasion when a club outside the top division of English football won
the FA Cup.
